hands_on_practices.solution:
We solve $AX=B$ by back substitution. Writing the equations row by row:

Row 4:
$$4x_4 = -1$$
$$x_4 = -\frac14.$$

Row 3:
$$3x_3 - \frac34\,x_4 = 1$$
Substitute $x_4=-\tfrac14$:
$$3x_3 - \frac34\Bigl(-\frac14\Bigr) = 1
\;\Longrightarrow\;
3x_3 + \frac3{16} = 1
\;\Longrightarrow\;
3x_3 = 1 - \frac3{16} = \frac{13}{16}
\;\Longrightarrow\;
x_3 = \frac{13}{48}.$$

Row 2:
$$2x_2 - \frac23\,x_3 + \frac12\,x_4 = -1$$
Substitute $x_3=\tfrac{13}{48}$, $x_4=-\tfrac14$:
$$2x_2 - \frac23\cdot\frac{13}{48} + \frac12\cdot\Bigl(-\frac14\Bigr) = -1
\;\Longrightarrow\;
2x_2 - \frac{13}{72} - \frac18 = -1
\;\Longrightarrow\;
2x_2 - \frac{11}{36} = -1
\;\Longrightarrow\;
2x_2 = -1 + \frac{11}{36} = -\frac{25}{36}
\;\Longrightarrow\;
x_2 = -\frac{25}{72}.$$

Row 1:
$$x_1 - \tfrac12\,x_2 + \tfrac13\,x_3 - \tfrac14\,x_4 = 1$$
Substitute $x_2=-\tfrac{25}{72}$, $x_3=\tfrac{13}{48}$, $x_4=-\tfrac14$:
$$x_1 + \frac{25}{144} + \frac{13}{144} + \frac{1}{16} = 1
\;\Longrightarrow\;
x_1 + \frac{47}{144} = 1
\;\Longrightarrow\;
x_1 = \frac{97}{144}.$$

Thus
$$X=\begin{pmatrix}\frac{97}{144}\\ -\frac{25}{72}\\ \frac{13}{48}\\ -\frac14\end{pmatrix}.$$

We compute the requested expression:

$$
x_1 - x_2 + x_3 - x_4
= \frac{97}{144} + \frac{25}{72} + \frac{13}{48} + \frac{1}{4}
= \frac{222}{144}
= \frac{37}{24}.
$$
